Class SyntheticAnnotationTypeElement

java.lang.Object
org.microbean.construct.element.SyntheticAnnotationTypeElement
All Implemented Interfaces:
AnnotatedConstruct, Element, Parameterizable, QualifiedNameable, TypeElement
public final class SyntheticAnnotationTypeElement extends Object implements TypeElement
An experimental TypeElement implementation that is wholly synthetic and suitable only for (partially) modeling annotation types.
Author:
Laird Nelson

  • Constructor Details

    • SyntheticAnnotationTypeElement

      public SyntheticAnnotationTypeElement(List<? extends AnnotationMirror> annotationMirrors, String fullyQualifiedName, List<? extends SyntheticAnnotationTypeElement.SyntheticAnnotationElement> elements)
      Creates a new SyntheticAnnotationTypeElement.
      Parameters:
      annotationMirrors - a List of AnnotationMirrors modeling the annotations this element has; must not be null
      fullyQualifiedName - the fully qualified name of the synthetic element; must conform to Java classname restrictions; must not be null
      elements - a List of SyntheticAnnotationTypeElement.SyntheticAnnotationElements modeling the annotation elements; must not be null
      Throws:
      NullPointerException - if any argument is null
      IllegalArgumentException - if fullyQualifiedName does not conform to Java classname restrictions
      See Also:
      • SyntheticAnnotationTypeElement.SyntheticAnnotationElement
      • SyntheticAnnotationMirror
